The paper deals with video deblurring, which is a problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of semantic segmentation and motion models suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also deals with optical flow, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of non-linear kernel models suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with complex models and algorithms.
